items.title: A lot changed this week at OpenAI. Elon Musk calls it a 'facade.'
items.description: It's been a busy week for AI upstart OpenAI. Not only did the company abandon plans to convert itself into a for-profit enterprise, but it also appointed Instacart CEO Fidji Simo as its new head of applications.

items.title: Cisco, Walmart Set To Report Results As Markets Watch Out For Core CPI
items.description: Retail giant Walmart is set to report earnings this week along with Cisco and Hertz Global. Read here for key stock market events this week.

items.title: MSFT, PLTR, and NVDA: Daniel Ives Picks the Best AI Stocks to Buy
items.description: AI promises to transform nearly everything about our world, in ways possibly more profound than anything since the Industrial Revolution kicked off in the 1760s. The technology is already automating the mundane tasks of the digital world, speeding up data collection and analysis and making results available at the press of a button.
